{"author":"Joe Oakhart","data":{"fields":{"description":"## What\n\nGenerate `docs/mcp-reference.md` from the MCP server's OWN registrars, correctly\nclassified by gate, and gate it in CI. Mirrors the `gen_env_registry.py` generator +\ndrift-gate pattern.\n\n## Source of truth (verified — registration-time vs call-time gating)\nThe server (`src/rebar/mcp_server.py` `build_server()`) assembles THREE registrars:\n- `register_read_tools` (`_mcp_reads.py`) — 23 tools, ALWAYS registered.\n- `register_llm_tools` (`_mcp_llm.py`) — 6 tools, ALWAYS registered; gated at CALL time on\n  `REBAR_MCP_ALLOW_LLM`.\n- `register_write_tools` (`_mcp_writes.py`) — 18 tools, CONDITIONALLY registered: returns\n  early when `REBAR_MCP_READONLY` is truthy, so they are ABSENT from `list_tools()` in\n  read-only mode. Totals verified: 47 tools (readonly off) / 29 (readonly on).\n\n**Critical:** only `REBAR_MCP_READONLY` changes list membership. `REBAR_MCP_ALLOW_LLM` and\n`REBAR_MCP_ALLOW_JIRA_SYNC` are call-time only (tools always listed, refuse at call). So a\nnaive single `list_tools()` in ambient env silently produces a PARTIAL reference. The\ngenerator MUST enumerate each registrar with `REBAR_MCP_READONLY=0` so writes register.\n\n## Classification rule (deterministic — registrar default + closed 3-entry special-case table)\nThere is NO per-tool gate attribute, and `readOnlyHint`/`destructiveHint` do NOT map to the\nenv gate. Classify by which registrar registers the tool, then apply the closed override table:\n| Group (registrar) | Default gate | Special-case overrides |\n|---|---|---|\n| READS | none (always available) | `reconcile` -> mutating modes blocked by `REBAR_MCP_READONLY` FIRST, then require `REBAR_MCP_ALLOW_JIRA_SYNC` (BOTH gate live mode; dry-run always works); `fsck` -> recover path gated by `REBAR_MCP_READONLY` |\n| LLM | `REBAR_MCP_ALLOW_LLM` (call-time) | `sign_review` -> `REBAR_MCP_READONLY` (HYBRID: in the LLM registrar but write-gated, makes no LLM call) |\n| WRITES | `REBAR_MCP_READONLY` (registration-time; absent when readonly) | `run_workflow` -> write-gated by `REBAR_MCP_READONLY` AND, for a non-dry-run workflow that HAS LLM steps, additionally gated at call time by `REBAR_MCP_ALLOW_LLM` (a second hybrid) |\n\nThis special-case table is CLOSED at FOUR entries (`reconcile`, `fsck`, `sign_review`,\n`run_workflow`); the generator carries them explicitly and a drift check asserts these four\nnames still exist in their expected registrars, so a new hybrid is caught rather than\nsilently misclassified.\n`sign_manifest` is a WRITE-registrar tool (not the LLM `sign_review` — do not conflate).\nGate descriptions come from the `MCP_ENV_VARS` constant (`mcp_server.py`), the same source\n`rebar-mcp --help` uses, so the doc cannot drift from `--help`.\n\n## Scope\n- Add `scripts/gen_mcp_reference.py` (new): enumerate each registrar onto its own FastMCP\n  with `REBAR_MCP_READONLY=0` (writes register); read each tool's name + first-line summary\n  (from `.description`); classify via the table above; emit `docs/mcp-reference.md` with a\n  generated header and exactly THREE clearly-labeled gate-tier sections:\n  **Read-only (always)**, **LLM-gated (`REBAR_MCP_ALLOW_LLM`)**, and\n  **Write-gated (`REBAR_MCP_READONLY`)**. The three special cases are inline ANNOTATIONS,\n  NOT separate sections: `reconcile` under Read-only annotated \"live/mutating modes blocked by\n  `REBAR_MCP_READONLY` and require `REBAR_MCP_ALLOW_JIRA_SYNC`\"; `fsck` under Read-only annotated \"recover path gated by\n  `REBAR_MCP_READONLY`\"; `sign_review` under Write-gated (NOT LLM-gated) annotated \"hybrid: in the LLM registrar,\n  write-gated\"; `run_workflow` under Write-gated annotated \"live LLM-step workflows also\n  require `REBAR_MCP_ALLOW_LLM`\". Include the `MCP_ENV_VARS` gate descriptions.\n- `--check` drift mode + CI gate in BOTH `.github/workflows/test.yml` AND\n  `.github/workflows/gerrit-verify.yaml` (the actual Verified gate; a parity test\n  `tests/unit/test_ci_workflow_parity.py` enforces every `scripts/*.py` in test.yml also\n  appears in gerrit-verify.yaml — omitting it breaks `make test`).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `docs/mcp-reference.md` is generated (marked generated) from the live registrars and\n      lists all 47 tools (23 read + 6 llm + 18 write).\n- [ ] Tools are structurally separated into labeled sections by gate tier (NOT prose) — a\n      Read-only section, an LLM-gated section, and a Write-gated section each exist (verify,\n      prints nothing):\n      `for s in 'Read-only' 'LLM-gated' 'Write-gated'; do grep -qi \"$s\" docs/mcp-reference.md || echo \"NO SECTION $s\"; done`\n- [ ] The three special cases are correctly placed — DETERMINISTIC section-bounded proof\n      (all three sub-checks print nothing). `sign_review` is in the Write-gated section and\n      NOT in the LLM-gated section; `reconcile` is annotated jira-gated; `fsck` annotated\n      readonly-recover:\n      `python scripts/gen_mcp_reference.py`\n      then a held-out unit test asserts, using section-bounded slicing of\n      `docs/mcp-reference.md` (awk from a tier heading to the next `## `): `sign_review` row\n      is inside the Write-gated section and absent from the LLM-gated section; the `reconcile`\n      row text contains BOTH `REBAR_MCP_READONLY` and `REBAR_MCP_ALLOW_JIRA_SYNC`; the\n      `run_workflow` row (Write-gated) text contains `REBAR_MCP_ALLOW_LLM`; the `fsck` row text contains\n      `REBAR_MCP_READONLY`. (The section-bounded assertion is the independent oracle — it\n      does not just re-run the generator's own classifier.)\n- [ ] Count proof (deterministic, prints nothing):\n      `python scripts/gen_mcp_reference.py && [ \"$(grep -cE '^\\| ?`?[a-z_]+`? ' docs/mcp-reference.md)\" -ge 47 ] || echo \"TOO FEW TOOLS\"` (or an equivalent explicit count of listed tool rows >= 47).\n- [ ] Drift gate works — adding/removing a tool changes output; a stale committed file fails\n      `--check` (deterministic, prints `CAUGHT`):\n      `python scripts/gen_mcp_reference.py; printf '\\nstale\\n' >> docs/mcp-reference.md; python scripts/gen_mcp_reference.py --check >/dev/null 2>&1 && echo MISS || echo CAUGHT; python scripts/gen_mcp_reference.py`\n- [ ] The gate is wired in BOTH CI files (prints nothing):\n      `for f in .github/workflows/test.yml .github/workflows/gerrit-verify.yaml; do grep -qF 'gen_mcp_reference.py' \"$f\" || echo \"NOT WIRED: $f\"; done`\n      and `python -m pytest tests/unit/test_ci_workflow_parity.py -q` passes.\n- [ ] `make lint && make typecheck && make test` stay green.\n\nFiles: `scripts/gen_mcp_reference.py` (new), `docs/mcp-reference.md` (new/generated),\n`.github/workflows/test.yml`, `.github/workflows/gerrit-verify.yaml`."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783830093147757001,"uuid":"496fd940-db4c-406f-93af-04c1bd8eba72"}